    • Method Detail

      • initializeAndUpgradeCAs

        void initializeAndUpgradeCAs()
        A method designed to be called at startup time to speed up the (next) first request to a CA. This method will initialize the CA-cache with all CAs, if they are not already in the cache. Can have a side-effect of upgrading a CA, therefore the Required transaction setting.

      • initializeAndUpgradeCA

        void initializeAndUpgradeCA​(Integer caid)
                     throws CADoesntExistsException
        Method that loads a CA in order to possibly upgrade it, in a separate transaction. This method is called from initializeAndUpgradeCAs in order to limit the transaction scope of CA upgrades.
        Parameters:
        caid - The CA to load/upgrade
        Throws:
        CADoesntExistsException - is the CA does not exist

      • healthCheck

        String healthCheck()
        Used by health-check. Validate that CAs are online and optionally performs a signature test.
        Returns:
        an error message or an empty String if all are ok.

      • getAuthorizedKeyValidatorIds

        Set<Integer> getAuthorizedKeyValidatorIds​(AuthenticationToken admin)
        This method returns a set containing IDs of all authorized key validators. This set will be the sum of the following: * Unassigned key validators * Key validators assigned to CAs that the administrator has access to.
        Parameters:
        admin - admin
        Returns:
        a Set of IDs of authorized key validators.
